4.47,6.9,5,4.25,4.5,4,4.75,"I have never tried this beer before this year (2014), and some of the reviews in the past seem to point out that, while Hoptimum tastes great, the smell is lacking. Well Sierra Nevada must have seen those review and adjusted the recipe because this beer smells great! Drink this beer from a snifter, and you won't want to pull the glass from your nose. This is also a beautiful looking beer! It has a golden, orange color to it that is extremely appealing. This may be the prettiest beer I have seen, what with the orange color and with a nice, off-white head. This beer is moderately carbonated, with a strong citrus taste (limes, grapefruit), and some nice piney notes. The flavor is (obviously) weighted on the hoppy side, but this is still nicely balanced. There is some alcohol feel, but it isn't over-powering (for me anyways). Overall this beer is fantastic, and one of the best Imperial IPAs I've tasted. I strongly recommend picking up a four pack if you see it!","JosephFlores","May 20, 2014"
